Trefi in [[Welsh]] or Trevi in [[English]] is derived from the term for a person from the [[Trevethin]] area of [[South Wales]]. It is commonly used derogatorally, as [[chav]], [[townie]] or [[pikey]], but sometimes it is simply an abbreviation denoting a native of the town.

